Interface ElementDisplayable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Element, EventBased
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ElementBrick, ElementButton, ElementCounter, ElementInfo, ElementItem, ElementList<T>, ElementMap<T>, ElementMultiButton, ElementSelector, ElementSizeable, ElementSwitcher<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CraftElementBrick, CraftElementButton, CraftElementCounter, CraftElementDisplayable, CraftElementInfo, CraftElementItem, CraftElementList, CraftElementMap, CraftElementMultiButton, CraftElementSelector, CraftElementSizeable, CraftElementSwitcher, Elements.ElementBrickExtendable, Elements.ElementButtonExtendable, Elements.ElementCounterExtendable, Elements.ElementDisplayExtendable, Elements.ElementItemExtendable, Elements.ElementListExtendable, Elements.ElementSizeableExtendable, Elements.ElementSwitcherExtendable

    public interface ElementDisplayable
extends Element
    With this element you can change the display of the element. If the element is disabled, the getDisabledIcon() will be displayed.
    Since:
    2.3.3
    Author:
    Rincewind34
    See Also:
    ElementSizeable
